claim.claim-text:
A method to produce an electrolyte for a fuel cell comprising the electrolyte material according to any one of claims 1 to 8, comprising the steps of:
● arranging a substrate in an angle of between 70 and 110, preferably between 80 and 100 and most preferably in a right angle, with a face through which the ionic current between the cathode and the anode of the fuel cell is to flow;
● growing the layer structure of the electrolyte material as a film on the substrate.
